result.execSummary:
The defendant Tracy B. Hampton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tracy B. Hampton is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tracy B. Hampton was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:33 a.m. Defendant Tracy B. Hampton in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Calling 15ct68, 15cm218 and 16cm163. In 15ct68, State moves to amend Count 1 to Negligent Operation of a Motor Vehicle, a violation of 941.01(1)-A Class A Misdemeanor. Voorhees statement to facts under 967.055 - Court finds that sufficient facts exist and grants amendment to OWI charge. State moves to dismiss Count 2 - Granted. In 15CM218, State moves to dismiss - Granted. In 16CM163, State moves to dismiss Count 2 - Granted. Defendant enters no contest plea to remaining counts.   Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty. Schiek/Voorhees/Defendant/Court statement to sentencing. 
Court Sentence
15ct68
Court imposes fine of $2,000 (includes costs)

16cm163
Court imposes fine of $1,000 (includes costs)

Cash bond posted in 15cm218 (apply towards 15ct68) and 16cm163 to be applied to fines. Defendant will pay balance of fines today.
Appeal rights given. Payment plan application given.
Adj. 10:15 a.m.

1:45 p.m. Defendant Tracy B. Hampton in court, via video, in custody.  Michael Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  In receipt of complaint, right to counsel - defendant will seek counsel, Schiek/Defendant statement to bail - Court sets $1000 cash bond. Adj. 1:52 p.m.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for April 11, 2018 at 08:30 am.
